



podman pod create --name sql-pod -p 9876:80 -p 5432:5432

podman run -d --pod sql-pod \
  --name postgres-db \
  -e POSTGRES_USER=admin \
  -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=mypassword \
  docker.io/library/postgres:latest

podman run -d --pod sql-pod \
  --name pgadmin-ui \
  -e PGADMIN_DEFAULT_EMAIL=admin@example.com \
  -e PGADMIN_DEFAULT_PASSWORD=adminpass \
  docker.io/dpage/pgadmin4:latest




Open your browser and go to http://localhost:9876.
Log in with the credentials used in Step 3 (admin@example.com / adminpass).
Click Add New Server.
In the Connection tab:
Host name/address: localhost (because they share the same pod network).
Port: 5432.
Username: postgres.
Password: The password set in Step 2 (mysecretpassword). 

